      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in input parameters (fluid properties, geometric tolerances) must be propagated through the model to bound QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Formal uncertainty propagation on model inputs is not required at MRL 2. Nominal fluid properties from published sources are used. Geometric tolerances are captured through the parametric dimension study. Factor not assessed; acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Statistical characterization of variability across experimental test samples must be documented.",
      "rationale": "The FDA pump dataset provides mean experimental values without full sample-level statistical breakdown at this assessment level. Variability characterization beyond reported means is not required at MRL 2. Factor not assessed; acceptable."
